Gene ontology enrichment of TWAS clusters

Yongjin Park

2018-08-09 14:01:13

We tested significant over-representation of the gene ontology (GO) terms1,2 within each trait cluster, using 3,139 all the heritable genes identified in this work as a background set. We downloaded mapping between genes and GO terms using biomaRt and its R interface3,4 (ENSEMBL version 79). We restricted our tests on 1,250 GO terms with a reasonable set size, ranging between 5 and 500 after intersecting them with the heritable genes.

Gene Ontology enrichement on TWAS clusters shows disnticitive biological processes.

Of the tested 1,250, total 157 GO terms are significantly over-represented with family-wise error rate cutoff 0.05, and we highlight the 68 terms in biological process with nominal p-value \(<\) 1e-5, sampling at most three most enriched categories from within each cluster (Fig.).

References

2. The Gene Ontology Consortium. Expansion of the gene ontology knowledgebase and resources. Nucleic Acids Res. 45, D331D338 (2017).

3. Durinck, S. et al. BioMart and bioconductor: A powerful link between biological databases and microarray data analysis. Bioinformatics 21, 34393440 (2005).

4. Durinck, S., Spellman, P. T., Birney, E. & Huber, W. Mapping identifiers for the integration of genomic datasets with the R/Bioconductor package biomaRt. Nat. Protoc. 4, 11841191 (2009).
